body:
The official name of Markdown on GitHub is GitHub Flavored Markdown, which has been extended by default Markdown.

This time, apply GitHub csss of highlight.js to convert Markdown text to HTML.

[GitHub Flavored Markdown)]

library used this time

-  [highlight.js]
-  [marked.js]


### Introduction

```bash
$ npm i highlight.js marked
```
Please install `crypto- es` at the same time.

### Convert GFM to HTML

Convert Markdown text to HTML and set highlight.jsjss to the code block.

```ts
import { marked } from 'marked';
import hljs from 'highlight.js';

const gfm_text = ""

marked.setOptions({
  highlight: function (code, lang) {
    const language = hljs.getLanguage(lang) ? lang : 'plaintext';
    return hljs.highlight(code, { language }).value;
  },
  langPrefix: 'hljs language-',
  gfm: true,
  breaks: true,
});

markd.parse(gfm_text)
```

## highlight.js

style.scss

```scss
@import '~highlight.js/styles/github.css';
```

 - - - 

You can see Markdown on GitHub. If the background- color of the code block is not present, please add grounds as appropriate.

```scss
:host ::ng-deep pre > code {
  background-color: #f6f8fa;
  border-radius: 10px;
}
```

 - - - 

tips: You can also override and customize renderer in the following ways:

```ts
import { marked, Renderer } from 'marked';
import crypt from 'crypto-es';
import hljs from 'highlight.js';

const renderer = new Renderer();
/** ヘッダーにはテキストのhash値から生成したフラグメント, リンクをコピーするボタンを追加する */
renderer.heading = (text, lebel) => {
  const hash = crypt.MD5(text);
  return `
  <div class="d-flex">
    <h${lebel}
      id=${hash}
      style="border-left: solid 3px; border-color: darkturquoise; border-radius: 2px; padding-left: 5px;"
    >${text}</h${lebel}>
    <button class="btn btn-sm">
      <i class="bi bi-clipboard" onclick="window.navigator.clipboard.writeText('${window.location.origin}${window.location.pathname}#${hash}')"></i>
    </button>
  </div>
  `;
};
/** img要素にloading lazyを追加する */
renderer.image = (href) => `<img src=${href} loading=lazy />`;
/** リンク要素にbootstrap iconのリンクマークを付与する */
renderer.link = (href, title, text) =>
  `<a href=${href} class="text-muted">${text}<i class="bi bi-link-45deg"></i></a>`;
marked.setOptions({
  renderer,
  highlight: function (code, lang) {
    const language = hljs.getLanguage(lang) ? lang : 'plaintext';
    return hljs.highlight(code, { language }).value;
  },
  langPrefix: 'hljs language-',
  gfm: true,
  breaks: true,
});

```

This could render GFM.

See [here] (https://github.com/kemu3007/portal/blob/master/portal/src/app/shared/markdown/marked.service.ts) for the actual source code you are using.

